Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.08,0:00:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad to have met you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's earthenware\Nis second to none!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the mystery is on\Nthe national treasure level!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.11,0:00:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.76,0:00:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.71,0:00:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.08,0:01:54.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:01:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You got a\Ncall from Kikuemon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.88,0:02:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! From the very man himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.10,0:02:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Kikuemon again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've never heard of Kikuemon,\Nthe living national treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a potter, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I thought he was a\Nkabuki actor or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.19,0:02:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did someone\Nso great want with you, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.15,0:02:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd give\Ndetails when we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants me to visit him in\NWest Tama this Sunday with my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With your family? I guess\Nit's not about hiring you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.09,0:02:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being with the family\Nmight be a type of camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.93,0:02:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Camouflage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.43,0:02:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep others from realizing\NI'm investigating a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.85,0:02:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably wanted to come\Nhere himself, but he is almost 80!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're so good at\Nreading into things, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Kikuemon-{\i1}san {\i0}is a living\Nnational treasure of pottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a living national\Ntreasure of detectiving!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that optimistic personality\Nis on the national treasure level...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Famous Potter Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This color, this shape...\Nit's a true masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I'd expect from the\Nwork of a living national treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't call me a national treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.17,0:03:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a person, not a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:51.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kikuemon (78) (Tsuchiya Mankichi) Ceramic Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this isn't much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sponge cake! Wonderful!\NI just love it! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did you need to see me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need me to see if\Nyour young wife is having an affair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. She's my son's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.52,0:04:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been taking care\Nof things for me for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sadly, my wife and son both died\Nin a car accident two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to hear it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've asked you\Nhere for but one reason:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to ask the opinion of the great\Ndetective everyone is talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've noticed your deductions\Nas of late have been so full of flaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F-Flaws?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! For example,\Nthe case last month--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! Don't act haughty, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just be honest and say you're a big fan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:05:00.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuchiya Masuko (42) Kikuemon's son's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.02,0:05:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the great Mori Kogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Masuko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.53,0:05:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a big fan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He gets so excited whenever\NMori-{\i1}san {\i0}solves a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.32,0:05:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, he just put up a big fuss
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.33,0:05:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I forgot to file an article\Nfrom the other day about a case of his!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Come, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, yeah, it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! It's really him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My pupils. Let me introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Arita-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:35.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Arita Yoshihiko (36) Kikuemon's pupil
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His skill has made leaps and bounds,\Nand his work shows promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.47,0:05:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.48,0:05:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand is Seto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.48,0:05:40.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto Ryuichi (35) Kikuemon's pupil
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His works have dropped in number,\Nand he's stuck in a standstill.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just in a slump, that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.28,0:05:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get for\Nalways copying our master!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.11,0:05:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, pull yourself\Ntogether, Seto-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.41,0:05:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're to be the sixth-generation\NKikuemon, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.75,0:05:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixth-generation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kikuemon name has been\Npassed down from master to pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the fifth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, tell us what kind\Nof pottery Detective Mori chose!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.14,0:06:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your horses!\NI still haven't told him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to have one of my works.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've brought one to your office,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wanted you to choose one for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.44,0:06:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, make your choice.\NAny of the ones in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all masterpieces,\Nworth millions of yen each!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Millions?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Dad. This is too generous.\NShow some restraint, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.05,0:06:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll just choose this cup!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I'd expect from a great\Ndetective! You have sharp eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I win the bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.19,0:07:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We all bet on\Nwhat you would choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.86,0:07:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, just as I expected\Nyou would, you chose that cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.83,0:07:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is hailed the\Nworld over as a masterware!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just dumb luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masterware indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.59,0:07:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never intended to give that away,\Nbut I don't mind in your case!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.84,0:07:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. I'd also like Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}to\Nsee the {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}, my latest work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you bring it from the storeroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes. Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.15,0:07:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come to think of it,\NI don't see Otani-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.57,0:07:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's by the kiln.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.11,0:07:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! Won't you come see the kiln?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:07:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:08:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, about how much is that cup worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. If it had a price, it'd maybe\Ngo for about 10 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.88,0:08:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10 million?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.80,0:08:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a joker!\NYou already knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have made that bet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.52,0:08:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's worth 10 million...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's a thousand 10,000 yen bills...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a big kiln!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it going, Otani-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I should be able to fire it before dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:46.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Otani Kaoru (36) Kikuemon's Pupil
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.21,0:08:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what is this pile of broken pieces?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.05,0:08:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The remains of pottery that the\Nlady of the house demolished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Demolished? By that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Despite how she seems,\Nshe has a very sharp eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.31,0:09:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, our master won't look at anything\Nthat doesn't meet her standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.85,0:09:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, she has the eyes that my son,\Nwho was to be my successor,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fell in love with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I've left\Nher in charge of deciding
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who will succeed the\NKikuemon name after I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But hasn't she been a bit strict lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have it good! She only okayed\Ntwo of my wares this month!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.17,0:09:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She hasn't okayed one\Nof mine in three months...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm at my limit now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any uncertainty in the heart\Nsoon shows up in earthenware.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.22,0:09:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any pottery made with such\Nfeelings will also be bent out of shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.94,0:09:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm your mind like the water\Nof a still lake, and it will naturally--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.86,0:09:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Was that her just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from the storeroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.88,0:10:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm so sorry! It tumbled down\Nwhen I went to climb the ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uhh, really, I didn't mean to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter. All that has\Nshape will someday break.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Fusui-maru {\i0}has\Nsimply returned to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.69,0:10:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You students can take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.69,0:10:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko-{\i1}san{\i0}, you can start\Non the nice meal for Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.95,0:10:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a tad exhausted.\NPlease don't wake me until dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be Otani's\N"everything gets broken" curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, do you need any help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we'll clean up here.\NYou can relax in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.91,0:11:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.53,0:11:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A marble?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.38,0:11:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had enough to drink!\NKeep it coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she a bad drunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, her personality\Nchanges whenever she drinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, is it really okay to\Naccept something so valuable?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to act reserved!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't long for this world, anyway!\NHe can't make much anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.03,0:12:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, I'm up there in age.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only make two or\Nthree decent things a year now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.08,0:12:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I seem to recall you\Nexhibited ten or so items last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind pottery! Let's hear\Nabout some more of your cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell us about\Nthe Tsukikage Island case!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna hear about the Kiri Tengu!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.60,0:12:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about the incident that\Nhappened during my class reunion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just told us that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the art museum\None and magician one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... That leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.82,0:12:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were the only three that\Nyou actually solved while conscious...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, you'll catch\Ncold if you sleep here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.46,0:13:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. She's not easily\Nwoken once she falls asleep drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well. I guess I'll carry her to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hurry back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.73,0:13:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the party\Ncontinued late into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seven people in the\Nstateroom forgot all their worries,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,drank up, and made merry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little did we know that a horrible\Nincident we'd never forget
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be waiting for\Nus in a few hours' time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? It's already 8:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to ask, but could\N you go wake Masuko-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to have some rice and tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.28,0:14:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You slept here too, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}! It's morning!\NMori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.12,0:14:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's deep asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he is "Sleeping Kogoro"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.17,0:14:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's a good point!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, her futon is empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. Where could she\Nhave gone this early in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she went to buy\Nsome things for breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we give her a call?\NShe did have a cell phone with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.07,0:14:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have anything too\Nheavy first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. She's not answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.01,0:15:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like pottery breaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.09,0:15:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! Don't tell me someone's\Ninside the storeroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.55,0:16:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She hanged herself just now!\NShe might survive if we get her down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.17,0:16:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get her legs!\NOtani, hold her steady!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll undo the rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.54,0:16:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lay her down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.55,0:16:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're too late! She's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master. Contact the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange! Those are missing, yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:16:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Tsuchiya Masuko, age 42.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.96,0:17:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wife of the son of Kikuemon-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nthe head of this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.80,0:17:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you were all in the stateroom\Nwhen you heard something break?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes. We had partied\Nlate into the night yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.18,0:17:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She went to sleep first,\Nso I carried her to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her futon was empty when\NI went to wake her this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.28,0:17:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just before we went to look\Nfor her, we heard something break,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.78,0:17:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when we rushed here, we found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.24,0:17:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound was of the pottery\Nthat's lying in pieces on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.79,0:17:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had probably stood\Non it when hanging herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.21,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been trampled on quite a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.67,0:17:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, Inspector. We stepped on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That little boy said she might\Nlive if we brought her down quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.60,0:18:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, soundly asleep as always\Ndespite just happening to be present...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is you again, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please don't shout. I have\Na hangover and my head is killing me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.62,0:18:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every place you go, there's a\Npile of dead bodies! Do you get it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.45,0:18:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.12,0:18:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. There are no signs\Nthat anyone climbed onto the beams.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ladder doesn't\Nreach to the roof beams, either;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something must've been tied to\Nthe end of the rope and thrown over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there seem to be plenty\Nof things to tie to it here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But would anyone use\Nsuch important works of art?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.81,0:18:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shelves don't hold just\Nthe master's work, but ours as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had used anything,\Nit probably would've been ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, these certainly are immaculate...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.08,0:19:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did spring cleaning not too long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.50,0:19:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the last remaining issue...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.29,0:19:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is this open cut on her calf.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.80,0:19:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There seems to have\Nbeen quite a lot of blood, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably messed up\Nand fell to the floor the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.26,0:19:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she did, she cut\Nher leg on a piece of the pot
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.60,0:19:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but ignored it and tried again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not uncommon for a noose\Nto be so big that the head slips out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or for a weak knot to come undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's blood everywhere\Nbecause she probably writhed around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm pretty sure we\Nonly heard one pot break...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.41,0:19:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then her first attempt must've\Nbeen while you were still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:19:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the rope had come untied,\Nit would've taken too long to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:20:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't seem like the type at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.22,0:20:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you think of any reasons?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was drinking so\Nhappily just last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She most likely did this out of\Nregret for breaking the {\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The poor woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fusui-maru{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.28,0:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The master's latest pot, which was\Nto be put on exhibition soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.83,0:20:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She broke it yesterday when\Nshe came to get it from the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.71,0:20:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had been\Ndeeply troubled by it, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.25,0:20:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it's not out of the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she had the motive and\Ncircumstances for this to be a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.14,0:20:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.02,0:20:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Examiner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please compare the cut with\Nthe shapes of the broken pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:20:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.48,0:21:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the pieces have\Nbeen trampled quite a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I can't say if any will match the cut...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A match would make\Nthis question go away, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide! It's clearly a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.41,0:21:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stepped on a broken piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.88,0:21:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you? You aren't\Nwearing anything on your feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it! I rushed here!\NThat lady's the same way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\NI don't see her footwear anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.85,0:21:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she came barefoot, the bottoms\Nof her feet should be dirty like mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.40,0:21:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.57,0:21:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nthe bottoms of her feet aren't dirty!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.86,0:21:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Then maybe\Nsomeone carried her here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.29,0:21:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:21:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're not saying--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.87,0:21:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was murdered, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.88,0:22:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then that places\Nthe suspicion on all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.95,0:22:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as you were in the nearby stateroom\Njust before the body was found!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.33,0:24:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.32,0:24:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.10,0:24:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found a trace\Nthat the killer failed to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.78,0:24:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this method, you wouldn't\Nneed to be in the room to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.23,0:24:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what did you find?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.13,0:24:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence that the killer\Nfailed to hide completely!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.27,0:24:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.68,0:24:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Famous Potter Murder Case (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.21,0:24:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.57,0:24:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lipstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.63,0:24:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode features a hidden pitfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.51,0:24:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't know it's there if you can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.97,0:24:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
